Steve Pikelny is a Brooklyn-based artist, engineer, and game designer. Using various digital and web-based media, his work generally explores money, the aesthetics of finance, blockchains, scams, misinformation, delusion, alternate realities, dark design patterns, internet subcultures, and existential dread caused by technology. Outside of his art practice, Pikelny is a serial entrepreneur, founding well known companies such as FinSexy.com, FastCashMoneyPlus.biz, RonaMetch.co, Friendworld.social, and FakeBullshit.news – all of which he continues to serve as the acting CEO, CTO, COO, and CFO. Additionally, he is a celebrated children’s book author and the maintainer of the largest Jesus pamphlet collection in North America.